Repository.
-----------
	- Repository used to collabrate the work flow.
	- GitHub is the Opne Source Repository Maintained by google.
	- "Git" is the Interface tool used to interact with the GitHub.

Installation Of Git.
--------------------
website : https://git-scm.com/download/win
file name : Git-2.13.2-64-bit.exe

GitHub Operations
-----------------
1. Create the repository locally.

2. Add the user credentials to repository.

3. create the files to the repository.

4. commit the files to the repository

5. create the branch

6. merge the branches

7. integration of github to the IDE'S
	1. Webstrom
	2. Ecilipse
	3. Visual Studio , VisualStudioCode

8. checkout the code from cloud repository.

9. push the code to the cloud repository

10.pull the code from cloud repository.



------------------------------------------------
1. Create the repository locally.
	
	- create the folder
		Ex.
			githubdemo

	- open the "gitbash here" terminal on rigth click on folder

	- execute the following command

	> git init

	[Note: automatically "githubdemo" initlized as a local repository]


2. Add the user credentials to repository.

> git config --global user.name "NareshIT"
> git config --global user.email "hr@nareshit.in" 


3. create the files to the repository.

>touch sample.js
	[Automatically "sample.js" file created to repository]


4. commit the files to the repository

> git status

> git add sample.js

> git commit

> press "i"

> type "initial commit"

> press "ESC"

> type ":wq"

> press "enter"


From 2nd Commit onwards folow the below commands to perform commit operation.

> git add sample.js
> git commit -m "Variables Created !"


5.create the branch
	>git branch AngularJS_10AM
	>git checkout AngularJS_10AM


6.Merge the Branch
	> git checkout master
	> git merge AngularJS_10AM


7.integration of github to the IDE'S

Download and install NodeJS
----------------------------
Website : https://nodejs.org/en/download/
file name : node-v6.11.1-x64.msi

we can check the node version by using followong command:
> node -v
O/P: v6.11.1


Download and Install IDE(WebStrom)
----------------------------------
website : https://www.jetbrains.com/webstorm/download/#section=windows
file name : WebStorm-2017.1.4.exe


Checkout the code from cloud repository
---------------------------------------
Git Url : https://github.com/ajsnaresh/AJS_Classes.git

- Run the Webstrom

- checkout code from repository

- github

- click the button "create API token"

- Enter the github login and password.

- click the "login" button

- enter the GitRepository URL and location to checkout code

- clone

- press "yes"

- by default we are in "master" branch.

- checkout the "angular2" branch

- we can see the project explorer by using "Alt+1"



9. push the code to the cloud repository.












